summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 2002 KEYSTONE OUTBACK.  THE CONTACT STATED THAT HIS REFRIGERATOR WAS REPAIRED ACCORDING TO THE DOMETIC RECALL; HOWEVER, HE DOES NOT FEEL THAT THE FAILURE HAS BEEN CORRECTED.  THE MECHANIC WHO REPAIRED HIS VEHICLE INFORMED HIM THAT IT WAS NOT SAFE BECAUSE A FIRE COULD STILL OCCUR AND THE COOLANT COULD STILL LEAK.  THERE HAD BEEN NO FAILURE TO DATE.  THE RECALL NUMBER AND REFRIGERATOR INFORMATION WERE UNKNOWN.  THE VEHICLE IS A PULL BEHIND TRAILER; THEREFORE, THERE IS NO VIN OR MILEAGE INFORMATION.
THE CONSUMER HAS A PROBLEM WITH RODENTS EATING THE WIRING INSULATION.  THE WIRING INSULATION WAS REPLACED AND THEY ARE EATING UP THE NEW REPLACEMENT WIRING AGAIN.  *JB
